{"name":"For the Confusion of the Tongue","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>If this spell is successful, it garbles the language of the affected person. The target can still think and, for the most part, act normally, but anything it says comes out as gibberish.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Persistence","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vjqBGvzPA1MGQVXU"}
{"name":"For to Conjure a Bolt from the Blue","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The caster can summon a lightning bolt from the heavens regardless of the weather. The bolt must strike a target outdoors in plain view. For to Conjure a Bolt from the Blue inflicts 3D6 points of damage, ignoring any Armour Points.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":3,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"Dodge","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GqhGO9h4gSsXkh6Z"}
{"name":"For to Count Many Things","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This allows the caster to accurately count a great number of similar things that are together in a mass &ndash; sacks of grain, muskets in an armoury, pikemen in an army. The caster must be able to see what is being counted and very precisely say what he is counting, otherwise the result may not be accurate. For instance, asking for &ldquo;the number of people in the enemy camp&rdquo; would include all the camp-followers, servants, etc., while asking for &ldquo;the number of soldier in the enemy camp&rdquo; would include any prisoners-of-war, and so on.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"pmgK9PUOMwU5Nlk5"}
{"name":"For the Encouragement of a Fanatical Mind","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>The target of this spell will have all Close Combat skills increased by +20%, but may not attempt to Parry or cast spells. The target will also have its Dodge skill halved. The effects of this spell are automatically cancelled by the spell For the Invocation of Fear, and vice versa.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":5,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6j4lwA5AWqqSK7Il"}
{"name":"For the Ignition of a Consuming Flame","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>This spell will set fire to anything readily flammable within range. Skin or flesh cannot be ignited, and if the target is attached to a living being (such as hair, fur or clothes) then the spell gains the Resist (Resilience) trait.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":false,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":true,"resist":"","touch":false,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ikbV7D01vEcCcDC5"}
{"name":"For the Ignition of the Fires of Passion","permission":{"default":0,"5OXcsyHbucZmXIwZ":3},"type":"spell","data":{"description":"<p>Gives the target the Seduction skill, or adds to the skill if the target already has it, for one single Seduction attempt. At Magnitude 1, this spell gives the target the Seduction skill at base level (INT+CHA), or adds +10% to an existing skill; each increase in Magnitude adds another 10% to the skill. It cannot be stacked with any other spell effect bonuses.</p>","skill":"0","area":0,"charm":false,"concentration":false,"distant":false,"duration":0,"eyeContact":false,"instant":true,"magnitude":1,"progressive":false,"ranged":false,"resist":"","touch":true,"trigger":false},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0kn3CXHbNgZrlPFd"}
